{
  "text": "Morphine inhibited spontaneous electrical activity of oxytocin-secreting neurons in the rat supraoptic nucleus [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , reducing plasma oxytocin [CITATION_3] . This effect was inhibited by administration of pertussis toxin [CITATION_4] or by stimulation of the anterior or ventral areas of the third ventricle [CITATION_5] , so that opiate mediation of oxytocin neurons may be complex. Modulation of phrenic nerve discharge amplitude also occurs after morphine, and the decrease is reversed by naloxone (36), suggesting splanchnic sympathetic regulation by the opiate.",
